import Mathlib

open Matrix

/-- If f : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ → ℝ is continuous and invariant under left-multiplication by orthogonal matrices, then f depends only on the Gram matrix Vᵀ ⬝ V. -/
theorem exists_continuous_g_of_orth_invariant (n : ℕ) :
  ∀ (f : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ → ℝ),
    Continuous f ->
    (∀ (U : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ), Uᵀ ⬝ U = 1 -> ∀ V, f (U ⬝ V) = f V) ->
    ∃ g : {A : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ // A.IsSymm ∧ Matrix.PosSemidef A} → ℝ,
      Continuous g ∧ ∀ V (h : (Vᵀ ⬝ V).IsSymm) (hp : Matrix.PosSemidef (Vᵀ ⬝ V)),
        g ⟨Vᵀ ⬝ V, And.intro h hp⟩ = f V := by sorry

import Mathlib

open Matrix

theorem exists_continuous_g_of_orth_invariant (n : ℕ) :
  ∀ (f : (Fin n → Fin n → ℝ) → ℝ),
    Continuous f ->
    (∀ (U : LinearIsometryEquiv ℝ (Fin n → ℝ) (Fin n → ℝ)), ∀ v, f (fun i => U (v i)) = f v) ->
    ∃ g : {A : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ // A.IsSymm ∧ Matrix.PosSemidef A} → ℝ,
      Continuous g ∧ ∀ v
        (h1 : (Matrix.of fun i j => Finset.univ.sum fun k => v i k * v j k).IsSymm)
        (h2 : Matrix.PosSemidef (Matrix.of fun i j => Finset.univ.sum fun k => v i k * v j k)),
        g ⟨Matrix.of fun i j => Finset.univ.sum fun k => v i k * v j k, And.intro h1 h2⟩ = f v := by sorry

import Mathlib

open Matrix

theorem exists_continuous_g_of_orth_invariant (n : ℕ) :
  ∀ (f : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ → ℝ),
    Continuous f ->
    (∀ (U : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ), Uᵀ * U = 1 -> ∀ V, f (U * V) = f V) ->
    ∃ g : Matrix (Fin n) (Fin n) ℝ → ℝ,
      ContinuousOn g {A | A.IsSymm ∧ Matrix.PosSemidef A} ∧
      (∀ V, g (Vᵀ * V) = f V) := by sorry
